- In this context, a project message refers to a specific category of messages related to work or collaborative projects; 
- The query aims to provide a comprehensive view of user engagement, covering both messaging and notification activities within a certain scope (project category or absence thereof); 
- Understanding the query's purpose can be enhanced by knowing that it is likely part of a larger system to monitor and analyze user interaction within a platform or application, possibly for the improvement of communication or project management tools.

- A thread is considered the basic unit of conversation in the messaging system; 
- Users can send and receive messages within these threads; 
- Notifications are generated based on user actions, such as sending or reading messages; 
- The system tracks whether messages are read or deleted for each user; 
- User activity is measured by their involvement in threads and the messages they send and receive.
